wikipedia_page.main: Harry Bradshaw (22 January 1895 – after 1923) was an English footballer.He was a goalkeeper at South Liverpool before moving to Tranmere Rovers. He played every game for Tranmere in the 1921–22 season, their first in the Football League. In 1923 he moved to Ellesmere Port Cement.
